     ----
* BEGIN VERBS
     ----
* VERBS
** parameters
*** -TENSE- there is no tense at all
*** NUMBER :: singular, plural
*** PERSON :: first, second, third
*** GENDER :: Sapient, insapient
*** VOICE :: active, passive
*** FRAME :: infinitive, finite, participle
*** MODE :: modals :: obligation, necessity, effort, desire, 
*** ASPECT :: perfect, imperfect, inchoative, cessative

* SIMPLE verbs
** a simple verb is a finite verb not marked for aspect 
*** thiktâlen kegot :: I touch the rock.
**** touch.fin.1s stone.acc
*** -thiktâltatos keg tumpash :: The rock is touched by the wind.-
**** -touch.fin.pass.3si stone air.abl-
**** thiktaxâlos keg tumpasht ::
**** The stone was touched by the wind.
**** note :: the agent in a passive clause is expressed by the ablative
**** thiktaxâlosen shevemenen tanashten ::
***** note /-emenen/ is not needed for verbs
***** note /-emenen/ :: /-emen/ is the possessor, -en is the number (plural)
***** /kenetemen/ our dog
***** /kenetemenen/ our dogs
**** touch.pass.fin.3si face.3ps man.abl.pl

* VOICE :: active, passive
** active verbs are not marked for voice
** that is to say, verbs not marked for voice are in active voice
***** a passive finite verb is marked with /kap/
***** ARCHAIC passive system
***** ARCHAIC -/tat/ goes between the finite verbal marker /âl/ and the pronominal suffix-
***** ARCHAIC -thiktâltatos keg tumpash :: The rock is touched by the wind.-
***** ARCHAIC -touch.fin.passive.3si stone air.abl-
***** ARCHAIC /kap/ goes immediately before the finite verb marker /âl/
***** ARCHAIC or the participle markers /az/, /ax/
***** ARCHAIC or the infinitive marker /âr/
***** ARCHAIC /kap/ may be preceded by an epenthetic /e/ to ease pronounciation
****** ARCHAIC given how Jagarôth consonants must be finished off, pronunciation will
       approximate an epenthetic /e/ anyway
***** ARCHAIC PASSIVE voice examples
****** -thiktikapâlos keg tumpasht- ::
** MODERN passive formations
*** passive voice in made from the passive participle
*** vê thiktaxâlos keg rorbasht :: the stone was touched by the Sun

* PARTICIPLES :: imperfect and perfect participles, passive participles
** participles function as either nouns/nominals or adjectives/adjectivals
***** ARCHAIC -the /kap/ system of participles died out sometime in the past-
***** ARCHAIC -hûdhitat or hûdhikapax-
***** ARCHAIC -note ::: epenthetic /i/ in hûdhikap-
** now in modern times /az/, /ax/ are used to form participles
** because hûdhikap ==> hûdhikapax ==> hûdhax, ditto /-az/
** _*ERGO*_ new system
** active participle
**** /thiktaz/ :: a touching thing, /thiktazik/ /adj./, touching
**** thiktax :: a touched thing, /thiktaxik/ /adj./ touched

* COMPLEX VERBS
** verbs may be formed in more complex ways
** /borgîzd/ in the town, /borgîzdâleth/ she is in town
*** /borgîzdâleth/ :: town.loc.fin.3ss
*** She is in town.
** vê thiktaxâlos keg rorbasht :: The stone was touched by the Sun.
*** when /-âl/ is thus appended, usually the meaning is "is whatever"
*** in-the-past touch.pass.fin.3si stone sun.abl
** vê rorb-thiktaxâlos keg :: the stone was sun-touched
*** vê rorb-thiktaxazâlos keg :: the stone was being suntouched/touched by the sun
**** /-axaz/ imperfect passive
**** in this case, /-ax/ creates a participle, /-az/ adds aspect
   ====

* TENSE -TENSE- there is no tense at all
** use adverbs and time nouns in the locative or accusative
*** locative to talk about a location in time
*** accusative to talk about a duration in time
* NUMBER :: singular, plural
** thiktâleth tan shevotem ::
** The man touches my face.
** thiktâlethen tanen shevotemen ::
** The men touch our faces.

* PRONOUNS and GENDER and NUMBER :: pronominal verbal endings
**   mem    :: -en   :: 1s 
**   memen  :: -enen :: 1p
**   teps   :: -eps  :: 2s
**   tepsen :: -epsen :: 2p
**   teth   :: -eth   :: 3s sapient
**   tethen :: -ethen :: 3p insapient
**   sos    :: -os    :: 3s sapient   
**   sosen  :: -osen  :: 3p insapient
** zed :: -ed :: reflexive, themself, themselves
** hemp :: -emp :: unspecified, unspec.
** totekek :: -ek :: reciprocal, one another, each other

* VERBAL suffixes
** suffix order
*** verbal + aspect + finite + voice + pronominal
** âl :: finite verbal suffix
** âr :: infinitive & gerund verbal suffix
** ax :: perfective aspect marker
** az :: imperfective aspect marker
** -um :: participial verbal suffix-
** thiktaz :: touching thing
*** thiktazik :: touching
** thiktax :: touched thing
*** thiktaxik :: touched
**** tat :: passive voice verbal suffix

* ASPECT
*** aspectuals in J. are particles and are used to describe an action's relation to time and movement through time
** /-az/ :: imperfect 
** /-ax/ :: perfect 
** /-apt/ :: inchoative
** /-anth/ :: cessative
** /-urth/ applicative is not an aspect
** /-ith/ causative is not an aspect

* MODALS/MODE
** modals are particles and are used instead of the modal verb + infinitive method of English to express grammatical mood
** hûn :: modal of moral obligation :: must
*** hûn borâleps!!! :: You must not do it!!!
**** moral-obligation not-do.fin.2s
** wûn :: hypothetical modal
** skrîn :: try modal
** kîn :: counsel modal, "should"
** tên :: desire modal
** fîn :: intention modal
** gûn :: hope modal


     ----
* END VERBS
     ----
     
     ----
* BEGIN NOUNS
     ----
* NOMINALS 
** CASE endings
*** nom :: -0 :: nominative
*** acc :: -ot :: accusative
*** gen :: -ûr :: genitive
*** dat :: -ôdh :: dative
*** abl :: -asht :: ablative
*** all :: -ov :: allative
*** ins :: -enth :: instrumental 
*** loc :: -îzd :: locative
*** com :: -eg :: comitative
*** car :: -ej :: caritive
** POSSESSOR endings
**** unlike the pronominal endings of verbs, possessor suffixes may be omitted
**** each of these denotes a /*singular noun*/, ergo:
**** -en must be added to the possessor suffix to get a plural noun
*** -em :: 1s
*** -emen :: 1p
*** -eps :: 2s
*** -epsen :: 2p
*** -eth :: 3ss (3rd sing. sapient)
*** -ethen :: 3ps (3rd plural sapient)
*** -os :: 3si (3rd sing. insapient)
*** -osen :: 3pi (3rd plural insapient)
*** -ed :: reflexive
*** -ek :: reciprocal
*** -emp :: unspec.
**** /-emp/ is often used creatively:
***** kenetemp :: a stray dog, one owned by unspec.

      ----
* END NOUNS
     ----

* RELATIVE clauses 
** relative clauses are opened with /ken/ + a resumptive pronoun
** and are closed with /wel/
** morbarkurthâlen totum kenetûren kensosen vipâlosen borgîzd mumbik wel
*** I shot one of the dogs that run in the dead city.
*** note :: /totum/ :: count nouns are literally concretized numbers
**** /tot-/ one + /-um/ thing
** îax klothorashtomin, tan kentethot morbarkurthâlen wel ::
*** BE-perfective law-ablative.human man REL-resumptive3ss-acc "to destruction".applicative.finite.1s ENDREL
*** The man I shot dead was an outlaw.
** vê zainurthâleth vâv weyumoteth, kensosot kebâleth gitôdheth wel 
** The woman salted her food, which she gave to her child.
** in-past-time salt.applic.fin.3ss woman eat.nominalizer.3ssP rel.3si.acc give.fin.3ss baby.dat.3ssP


* WORD ORDER
** word order is free but the default is VSO

