Trelishar :: nominal, personal name :: a Jagarôth baby girl's name *** in the
Jagarôth language's sphere of influence, connotes a typically and attractively
feminine person, often bestowed on children in that hope, or maybe just because
it sounds pretty ** vrî- :: sub-comparative verbal prefix :: "under"-<verbal>
*** corresponds to /skai-/ the super-comparative verbal prefix, "out" ***
vrî-layâlos Lûn rorbôdh :: under-radiate-FINITE-3sinsapient Moon Sun-DATIVE ***
"The Moon is less radiant/bright than the Sun." *** I don't really know what to
call these *** super/sub-comparative verbal prefix, major/minor-,
greater/lesser- ** konokin :: nominal :: a kind of alter-human/homin *** found
in small, often isolated and most often shunned communities throughout Sol
System, often contemned by the popular imagination's malice as beings of low
estate who merely subsist in the most undesirable locales only such as drifting
hulks and Oort cloud rocks *** what are they like? Frankly, they look like
walking corpses. They're skin is usually a dead white, save for the frequency
of blood-red birthmarks in the kônokin genetic pool. Also they do not wear
clothing and their faces are frozen grimaces almost entirely lacking in
muscular mobility. They cover their faces usually with faceless masks of great
or lesser terror, but terror. Their proportion and gait are ungainly and jerky,
and though they are the least violent of homin breeds all other homin fear them
as dark, uncanny entities possessed of uncouth but ultimately unknowable
abilities and powers. ** Sherîn :: nominal :: Martian female's name ** stom ::
